ton]]\n| [[John Glen (director)|John Glen]]\n| 191.2\n| 313.5\n| 40.0\n| 68.8\n| {{sfn|Block|Autrey Wilson|2010|pp=428\u2013429}}{{sfn|Cork|Scivally|2002|pp=300\u2013303}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Living-Daylights-The#tab=summary |title=The Living Daylights (1987) |website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Licence to Kill]]''\n| 1989\n| [[Timothy Dalton]]\n| [[John Glen (director)|John Glen]]\n| 156.2\n| 250.9\n| 36.0\n| 56.7\n| {{sfn|Block|Autrey Wilson|2010|pp=428\u2013429}}{{sfn|Cork|Scivally|2002|pp=300\u2013303}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=licensetokill.htm |title=Licence to Kill (1989) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[GoldenEye]]''\n| 1995\n| [[Pierce Brosnan]]\n| [[Martin Campbell]]\n| 352.0\n| 518.5\n| 60.0\n| 76.9\n| {{sfn|Block|Autrey Wilson|2010|pp=428\u2013429}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=goldeneye.htm |title=GoldenEye (1995) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Tomorrow Never Dies]]''\n| 1997\n| [[Pierce Brosnan]]\n| [[Roger Spottiswoode]]\n| 333.0\n| 463.2\n| 110.0\n| 133.9\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=tomorrowneverdies.htm |title=Tomorrow Never Dies (1997) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''{{sort|world|[[The World Is Not Enough]]}}''\n| 1999\n| [[Pierce Brosnan]]\n| [[Michael Apted]]\n| 361.8\n| 439.5\n| 135.0\n| 158.3\n| {{sfn|Block|Autrey Wilson|2010|pp=428\u2013429}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=worldisnotenough.htm |title=The World Is Not Enough (1999) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]]|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Die Another Day]]''\n| 2002\n| [[Pierce Bro