3&item=47&printable | accessdate = 16 March 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NYT: Sony & MGM\">\n{{cite news|title=Sony Pictures, in an accord with MGM, drops its plan to produce new James Bond films|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=30 March 1999|url= https://www.nytimes.com/1999/03/30/business/media-business-advertising-sony-pictures-accord-with-mgm-drops-its-plan-produce.html?n=Top%2fNews%2fBusiness%2fSmall%20Business%2fMarketing%20and%20Advertising|accessdate=16 March 2008 | first=James | last=Sterngold}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GG: TND\">\n{{cite web|title=The 55th Annual Golden Globe Awards (1998)|url=http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1997|work=Golden Globe Awards|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=27 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130415020047/http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1997|archivedate=15 April 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GG: DAD\">\n{{cite web|title=The 60th Annual Golden Globe Awards (2003)|url=http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/2002|work=Golden Globe Awards|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=27 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130414235034/http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/2002|archivedate=14 April 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GG: VTAK\">\n{{cite web|title=The 43rd Annual Golden Globe Awards (1986)|url=http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1985|work=Golden Globe Awards|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=27 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130415034920/http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1985|archivedate=15 April 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GG: No\">\n{{cite web|title=The 21st Annual Golden Globe Awards (1964)|url=http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1963|work=Golden Globe Awards|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=27 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130414233741/http:/