 the B.U.D.D.Y. System!\n |DirectedBy      = John Aoshima\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones}}\n |Aux2            = Benjamin Balistreri, Evon Freeman, Mark Garcia, Tanner Johnson & John Ramirez\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|11}}\n |ProdCode        = 114\n |Viewers         = 0.68<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-11-2018.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.11.2018&nbsp;\u2013 Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 14, 2018|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=May 14, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Launchpad finally receives his driver's license and goes with Dewey to show Scrooge, who is busy with Gyro and his bumbling intern, [[Fenton Crackshell-Cabrera]] ([[Lin-Manuel Miranda]]). Meanwhile, Beaks unveils a new [[self-driving car]], so Launchpad challenges Beaks' invention to a race to prove that men are better than machines. Even though he loses, it's revealed that Beaks stole Gyro's robot technology after Fenton posted it on the internet. Launchpad and Fenton both lose their jobs and end up humiliated. But when Scrooge, Dewey, Gyro, and Beaks become trapped inside the self-driving car, it's up to Launchpad and Fenton to save them; with the latter using Gyro's top secret project, a cybernetic suit, to become the robotic superhero \"[[Gizmoduck]]\". In the end, Launchpad gets his job back and earns Scrooge's recognition, Gyro lets Fenton use his invention permanently, and Beaks plots to get Gizmoduck for his own company. \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n |Title           = The Missing Links of Moorshire!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Ben Joseph, Christian Ma