ow up the vault. Della and Dewey sneak off to see the seeds before Scrooge seals the vault, but accidentally cause mayhem and severely add to the damage. Dewey blames himself, but Della, using the skills she learned on the Moon, saves the situation and assures her son that he'll never have to prove himself to her.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 37\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n |Title           = Friendship Hates Magic!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes, Bob Snow & Rachel Vine|t=Vine}} \n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Victoria Harris, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|5|15}}{{efn|name=ep214|This episode made its broadcast premiere on [[Disney Channel (Dutch TV channel)|Disney Channel Netherlands]] on April 28, 2019.}}\n |ProdCode        = 208\n |Viewers         = 0.33<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-15-2019.html|title=Top 150 Wednesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.15.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 16, 2019|access-date=May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Webby heads to the library to once again find a way to get Lena back from the Shadow Realm, still unaware that she has been watching over her. While there, she meets another supernatural enthusiast, Violet Sabrewing ([[Libe Barer]]), who suggests they have a sleepover to further discuss the realm. Amidst said sleepover, Lena becomes suspicious of Violet, learns she brought Magica's amulet, and tries to warn Webby. While trying to bring Lena back, Webby and Violet enter the Shadow Realm, where the former briefly reunites with Lena before she's captured by [[tulpa]]s that manifested from Lena's jealousy towards Violet. Together, Lena and Violet ward off the spirits, but this causes Lena to fade away too. 