 beat him with his \"Fentonium\"-powered ping-pong ball. Before she stealthily leaves, Gandra gives Fenton the equation he needed to stabilize said ping-pong ball.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 39\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 16\n |Title           = The Duck Knight Returns!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones}} \n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|5|17}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = 0.39<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-17-2019.html|title=Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.17.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 20, 2019|access-date=May 20, 2019}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = Launchpad and Dewey meet the washed-up star of ''Darkwing Duck'', Jim Starling ([[Jim Cummings]]), and learn Scrooge is making a movie based on the TV show with Alistair Boorswan ([[Edgar Wright]]) directing. After a disappointing trailer however, Scrooge puts Dewey in charge while Starling learns he's replaced by a younger actor, [[Drake Mallard]] ([[Chris_Diamantopoulos|Diamantopoulos]]). Starling convinces Launchpad to help him get rid of Drake so he can reprise his role, but the latter changes his mind upon realizing Drake is a genuine fan. Starling, on the other hand, remains unwilling to pass the torch and goes on a rampage throughout the set to finish the movie himself while Launchpad and Drake try to stop him. In the end, Starling seemingly sacrifices himself to save Launchpad and Drake from an accident he caused and Scrooge cancels the movie. Afterwards, Launchpad encourages Drake to become a real superhero in Starling's memory while Starling himself secretly survived, but [[Negaduck|went insane]].<!--HOLD OFF ON ACTUALLY CALLING HIM NEGADUCK UNTIL WE SEE HIM TAKE THE NAME-->\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 40\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 17\n |Title           = What Ever Happened to Donald Duck?!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = Jason Reicher & Jason Zurek\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Evanson}}\n |Aux2            = Jean-Sebastien Duclos, Victoria Harris, Sam King & Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|9|3}}{{efn|Beginning with this episode, new episodes of the show premiere on Disney XD instead of Disney Channel.}}\n |ProdCode        = 218\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = Lunaris passes off Donald as a spy and sends him to the gold mines. Not wanting the invasion to happen however, Penumbra secretly frees Donald and tells him to meet her at Lunaris' hangar so they can destroy the rocket fleet. When they eventually get there, they find that Lunaris has been planning to attack Earth long before Della came. Penumbra gives Donald a transmitter to warn Earth of the invasion before she's suddenly subdued. Lunaris appears and fights Donald after he threatens the boys' lives, but the latter is able to escape on the former's prototype rocket and return to Earth. Meanwhile, Dewey and Webby, wanting another mystery to solve, take up the case of Huey's returned postcard to Donald. Their investigation leads them to a man named [[Neighbor Jones|Jones]] ([[James Adomian]]), who they believe might be behind Donald's implied disappearance. They later find out that he was Donald's anger management counselor, who helped him channel his temper into protective instinct. After picking them up, Scrooge gets Donald's message, but couldn't understand it due to poor reception.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 41\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n |Title           = Happy Birthday, Doofus Drake!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      =  Ma