inals-9-6-2019.html|title=UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.6.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=September 9, 2019|access-date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = At Fort Duckburg, Webby convinces the boys to join her on an adventure to find [[Cornelius Coot]]'s golden armory; a treasure Della never found. They discover a secret mine entrance under Coot's statue, and using Della's journal, search for the treasure. Meanwhile, Big Time, who was kicked out of the Beagle Boys, follows them in the hopes of finding the treasure first and win back Ma's approval. Elsewhere, Della tries to get ready to sky-write over the fort, but has to repair the plane with Launchpad. The kids find the treasure, which turns out to be corn, disappointing Webby. They are taken hostage by the Beagles, but they are saved when Della and Launchpad crash into the mine. Webby resumes looking for clues, so Della goes after her while Big Time captures the others with an army of spiders. When Della finds her, Webby reveals her determination to be like her, but Della assures her that she is already a great adventurer. They then discover that Coot used the corn as makeshift artillery via giant popcorn poppers to imitate gunfire and scare his enemies into retreating. The group escape the cave, while Ma invites Big Time back into the gang.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 44\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 21\n |Title           = Timephoon!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = Jason Zurek\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Samir Barrett, Victoria Harris, Sam King & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|9|9}}\n |ProdCode        = 221\n |Viewers         = 0.15<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-9-2019.html|title=UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.9.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=September 10, 2019|access-date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Louie's latest \"get-rich-quick\" scheme, treasure hunting through time using Gyro's Time Tub, goes horribly wrong when it turns a local hurricane into a \"timephoon\", bringing people and animals from the past to the present. In an attempt to stop it, Louie returns the treasures, but it fails to work and he gets caught by Della. Things then go from bad to worse as each family member is sent to a different time period, leaving only Louie. In the end, with help from a caveduck named [[Bubba the Caveduck|Bubba]] ([[Dee Bradley Baker]]) Louie is able to return the time-displaced people and everyone comes back. However, while the others forgive Louie, Della grounds him for his actions. Afterwards Huey, who studied Bubba for an entry in his Junior Woodchuck Guidebook, ponders if he might have been an ancestor of Clan McDuck.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 45\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 22\n |Title           = GlomTales!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Evanson}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|9|10}}\n |ProdCode        = 222\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = Louie, who is still grounded, tries to escape the manor and join the family's latest adventure, but is constantly stopped by Della's countermeasures. Meanwhile, Glomgold, in a final attempt to win the bet before the deadline, teams up with the Beagle Boys, Beaks, Don Karnage, and Magica to invade the manor. Desperate, Louie tells Glomgold how to win in return for a partnership. The villains then confront the family and, as instructed by Louie, pool their resources just as time runs out, causing Glomgold to win the bet. However, since \"Glomgold\" is a fake identity, everything goes to Louie instead. The villains angrily turn on Glomgold, forcing him to flee. Della is happy Louie seemingly learned his lesson, but when she tells him to give Scrooge his company back, he hesitates.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 46\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 23\n |Title           = The Richest Duck in the World!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|9|11}}\n |ProdCode        = 223\n |Viewers         = 0.15<ref>http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-11-2019.html</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = After effectively winning the bet, Louie decides to keep Scrooge and Glomgold's companies and fortunes so he can live it up as \"The Richest Duck in the World\", until an emergency arises on a mysterious island. Traveling there with Owlson, Launchpad, and Manny, Louie finds the [[Bombie the Zombie|Bombie]] ([[Fred Tatasciore]]), a monster bent on destroying the world's richest person. They try to escape the creature, but it proves relentless. Louie eventually realizes the only way to stop the Bombie is to be humble, so he shines it's shoes with Scrooge and returns his company to him. Meanwhile, Della tries to make radio contact with Penumbra, though Dewey causes her to question if they were ever truly friends. Ultimately, Della does get a message from Penumbra, who reaffirms their friendship and warns her of Lunaris' invasion.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 47\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 24\n |Title           = Moonvasion!\n |RTitle          = {{efn|name=s2e24-25|This episode is a one-hour special.<ref name=\"WDTV September\" /> When aired as two half-hour episodes they were titled as \"Moonvasion! Part I\" and \"Moonvasion! Part II\".}}\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson & Jason Zurek\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Fransisco Agones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman, Evanson, Magalhaes & Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Kristen Gish, Victoria Harris, Ben Holm, Sam King, Kat Marusik, Stephan Park, William Ruzicka & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|9|12}}\n |ProdCode        = 224\n |Viewers         = 0.17<ref>http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-12-2019.html</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = As the Moonlanders' invasion begins, Scrooge gathers the family's allies for a counterattack. However, it fails and Lunaris reveals his plan to make the Earth revolve around the Moon using a planetary engine. Elsewhere, Della flies the kids to safety, disguising it as a recruitment drive, but they're attacked and crash on an island, where they find Donald. Della tries to sway the others from leaving, until Louie helps her see that it's okay to have bad experiences because there will be good ones. Gladstone and Fethry soon find them and take them back to Duckburg on Mitzi. Meanwhile, Scrooge reluctantly teams up with Glomgold and defeats Lunaris with a dumb, but successful plan. Lunaris flees in his ship and attempts to blow up the Earth, leading to a space battle against the Ducks. In the end, Penumbra arrives and damages Lunaris' ship, leaving him stranded in space. Afterwards, the Moonlanders stop the invasion and the family celebrates, unaware of F.O.W.L watching them.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 3 (2020) ===\n{{Episode table|background=#960018|overall=|season=|title=|director=|writer=|aux2=|aux2T=Storyboard by|airdate=|prodcode=|prodcodeR=<ref name=WDTV>{{cite web|url=https://www.wdtvpress.com/disneyxd/shows/ducktales/episodes/|title=Disney XD - DuckTales: Episode Info|website=Walt Disney Television Press|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>|viewers=|country=U.S.|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 48\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Challenge of the Senior Junior Woodchucks!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones & Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Krystal Ureta & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|4}}\n |ProdCode        =  304\n |Viewers         = 0.19<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-4-20.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.4.2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=April 7, 2020|access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = As part of their Junior Woodchuck graduation, Huey and Violet must compete in a challenge to earn the title of Senior Woodchuck. Panicked by the possibility of losing, Huey hallucinates a talking Junior Woodchuck guidebook ([[Stephen Root]]) to aid him and ignores Violet when she is endangered. After Violet saves his life, he admits she's a better Woodchuck and forfeits the competition. Meanwhile, Scrooge finds a map to the treasure of famed adventurer Isabella Finch, but his attempts to find it are thwarted when the rest of the family decide to follow a strange bird instead. While he insists they are missing out, the others remind him that it is more meaningful to have your own adventure than to follow someone else's. The bird ultimately leads them to Finch's treasure: her lost adventure journal which contains a list of legendary treasures she was unable to find. The group resolve to hunt the treasures down, unaware that F.O.W.L. is spying on them and plotting to claim them first.\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 49\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Quack Pack!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Kristen Gish & Victoria Harris\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|4}}\n |ProdCode        = 303\n |Viewers         = 0.19<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-4-20.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.4.2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=April 7, 2020|access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = While on an adventure to find the Lost Lamp of Collie Baba, Donald wishes for a normal life, unaware he was next to the lamp. Fulfilling Donald's wish, [[List of DuckTales characters#Gene the Genie|Gene the Genie]] ([[Jaleel White]]) sends the family into a '90s sitcom called ''[[Quack Pack]]'' and erases their memories. While focusing on taking the perfect family photo, Huey suspects something is wrong after hearing Donald's normal voice and slowly manages to convince the others. Donald tries his best to hide his secret by maintaining the plot and reluctantly hiring his wacky neighbor, [[Goofy]] ([[Bill Farmer]]), to be the photographer. The family eventually finds Gene and demand he send them back home, but he tells them only Donald can reverse the wish since he made it. Donald refuses and storms off with Goofy. When the others try to escape, the wish fights back to maintain itself. Using his son [[Max Goof|Max]] as inspiration, Goofy helps Donald realize that different families can have their own idea of \"normal\" before helping him save his. Amidst the chaos, Goofy finds the lamp and Donald uses his second wish to undo his first. With the last wish, he gets a framed picture of him and his family.\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 50\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Double-O-Duck in You Only Crash Twice!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = Jason Zurek\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Magalhaes}}\n |Aux2            = Sam King, Kat Marusik, Rachel Paek & Stephan Park\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|11}}\n |ProdCode        = 303\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = Webby gets Scrooge to visit Funso's, where Dewey and Launchpad play a VR spy game. Unbeknownst to them though, Funso's is actually a F.O.W.L. base and Director Bradford Buzzard ([[Marc Evan Jackson]]) orders agents Black Heron and Steelbeak ([[Jason Mantzoukas]]) to remove Scrooge before he finds out. However, Steelbeak captures Dewey and Launchpad, who continue to think they're in a game, increasing the likelihood of them being discovered. Heron intends to use an \"Intelli-Ray\" to make Scrooge dumb, only for Steelbeak to hijack the operation after she insults him and for Launchpad gain increased intelligence. Steelbeak then abducts Dewey and intends use the ray on all of Duckburg, but Launchpad is able to stop him with help from F.O.W.L.'s former [[Chip 'n Dale: Rescue Rangers|lab rats]] at the cost of his intelligence. Afterwards, Launchpad's stupidity prevents him from warning Scrooge about F.O.W.L. while Buzzard reprimands Heron and Steelbeak for almost compromising their plans.\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 51\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Lost Harp of Mervana!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|18}}\n |ProdCode        = 301\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = [[Retta]] guest stars as the Mystical Harp.\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 52\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Louie's Eleven!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|25}}\n |ProdCode        = 305\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = <!--No more than 200 words episode summary, written in your OWN words. Copy and pasting from Futon Critic / Walt Disney Television will be reverted as a copyright violation [[WP:COPYVIO]]-->\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 53\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Astro B.O.Y.D.!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|2}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 54\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = The Rumble for Ragnarok!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|9}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n|titleR=<ref name=TVAS3>{{cite tweet|number=1238861201775493120|title=Start your Saturday with some #DuckTales news! Here are the official titles & release dates for Season 3, Part 1  on @DisneyXD  Which are you most looking forward to?|user=DisneyTVA|date=March 14, 2020|accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref>|airdateR=<ref name=TVAS3 />}}\n\n==Online shorts==\n\n===Shorts overview===\n<onlyinclude>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n|+Shorts overview\n! colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\"| Online shorts\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Episodes\n! colspan=\"3\"| Originally aired\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Series premiere\n! scope=\"col\"| Series finale\n|-\n| style=\"background: #A52A2A;\"|\n| '''[[List of DuckTales (2017 TV series) episodes#Welcome to Duckburg!|Welcome to Duckburg!]]''' || 6 ||  June 9, 2017 || J