e and becomes the new captain. Following another attack on the McDuck plane, Dewey reconciles with his family, and helps regain Scrooge's treasure; leaving Karnage to swear vengeance.\n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 21\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 21\n |Title           = The Secret(s) of Castle McDuck!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Vaughn Tada, Brandon Warren & Jason Zurek\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|8|4}}\n |ProdCode        = 122\n |Viewers         = 0.73<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-8-4-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 8.4.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=August 7, 2018|access-date=July 17, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = To get to the [[Knights Templar]]'s treasure, Scrooge pays his parents, [[Fergus McDuck|Fergus]] and [[Downy O'Drake|Downy]] ([[Graham McTavish]] & [[Ashley Jensen]]), a visit. Because of his strained relationship with his father however, Scrooge sets out to find it himself. Along the way, he discovers that his father indirectly gave him his Number-One Dime via the ditch digger who gave it to him as a gift of \"self-reliance\", and the two reconcile. Meanwhile, Dewey struggles to keep his search for Della a secret from Huey and Louie. Upon Dewey\u2019s eventual confession, Huey and Louie are heartbroken, but eventually forgive him. Working together, they find an image of ''The Spear of Selene''.\n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 22\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 22\n |Title           = The Last Crash of the Sunchaser!\n |DirectedBy      = John Aoshima\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones