ate, only for the mystery to deepen when they discover that \"Glomgold\" is a fake identity. They then take Scrooge to meet him, but he decides to let him be, as he is happy. However, Glomgold ultimately regains his memory: born \"Duke Baloney\"; he was a shoeshine boy who did Scrooge's shoes and was paid with a dime to teach him self-reliance, only for him to feel cheated and create his \"Glomgold\" persona to get revenge. He then returns to his company and makes a bet with Scrooge: whoever's richer by the end of the year gets the loser's company.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 27\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Town Where Everyone Was Nice!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|10}}\n |ProdCode        = 204\n |Viewers         = 0.55<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-11-10-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 11.10.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=November 13, 2018|access-date=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The family visits a Brazilian town to celebrate the mysterious festival, \"The Feast of the Flower\". While there, Donald reunites with his old college buddies, [[Jos\u00e9 Carioca]] and [[Panchito Pistoles]] (Bernardo de Paula & [[Arturo Del Puerto]]). Finding that they each live a successful life however, Donald pretends to be a billionaire to impress them, with Scrooge and Huey playing along. Meanwhile, Webby tries to get Dewey and Louie to fully experience the festival, but they just want to take pictures. They all soon discover that the town's friendly locals are all part of a giant [[carnivorous plant]]. After Donald tells the truth, and learns that his friends also lied, [[The Three Caballeros]] reunite to fight the plant with music.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 28\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Storkules in Duckburg!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|17}}\n |ProdCode        = 205\n |Viewers         = 0.57<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-11-17-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 11.17.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=November 20, 2018|access-date=November 20, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Louie wants to start his own company, but can't decide on what kind. Meanwhile, Donald rents out a room on his houseboat and is surprised that Storkules, who was kicked out by his father, is the renter. However, the Greek hero soon finds that a flock of [[harpies]] followed him to Duckburg and are causing havoc. Seeing this as an opportunity, Louie starts a monster-control business, ''Harp-B-Gone'', with Huey, Webby, and Storkules. However, Storkules secretly stores them on the houseboat, and they eventually break free and take off with Donald. In the end, ''Harp-B-Gone'' saves Donald and recaptures the harpies. Louie realizes he let his success go to his head and disbands the business, giving the harpies to Scrooge to use as workers at a lemonade company after realizing their potential.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 29\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Last Christmas!\n |DirectedBy      = Jason Zurek\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones}}\n |Aux2            = Jean-Sebastien Duclos, Sam King & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|12|1}}\n |ProdCode        = 206\n |Viewers         = 0.53<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-12-1-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 12.1.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=December 4, 2018|access-date=December 4, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The family is celebrating Christmas, except for Scrooge and Dewey. In actuality though, Scrooge secretly goes back in time every Christmas to revisit his best parties with the [[Ghost of Christmas Past|Ghosts of Christmas Past]] ([[Jack McBrayer]]), [[Ghost of Christmas Present|Present]] ([[Bill Fagerbakke]]), and [[Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come|Future]]. However, he eventually realizes the real fun of Christmas is spending it with family. Past, on the other hand, doesn't want to let go of their fun times together and traps him in time, but Scrooge outsmarts him and escapes. Meanwhile Dewey, who secretly followed Scrooge to the past, ends up facing a [[wendigo]] with a younger Donald ([[Russi Taylor]]) and Della. They manage to capture it, after which it's revealed to be Past. Scrooge, who arrives to take Dewey back, then makes up with Past and they all return to the present to spend Christmas with the others. Meanwhile on the Moon, Della gives everyone her best wishes as she continues to fix her spaceship.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 30\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = What Ever Happened To Della Duck?!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s= Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman & Evanson}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|3|9}}\n |ProdCode        = 207\n |Viewer