om/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-13-2019.html|title=Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.13.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 14, 2019|access-date=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Della is reunited with her family, but has a tough time readjusting. While ranting about how to be a better mother, she accidentally reactivates The Gilded Man, [[El Dorado]]'s golden robot, which she defeated as a child. The robot attempts to kill Della, but with help from the boys and the rest of the family, she's able to defeat it once more. Afterwards, she promises to be the best mom she can be, and the boys embrace her. Meanwhile, Donald lands on the Moon and uses Oxy-Chew to save himself from suffocating, only to be taken prisoner by the Moonlanders. \n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 36\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n |Title           = Raiders of the Doomsday Vault!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}} \n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|5|14}}\n |ProdCode        = 214\n |Viewers         = 0.41<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-14-2019.html|title=Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.14.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 15, 2019|access-date=May 15, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Ludwig von Drake's Arctic doomsday vault \u2013 built as a safekeep in case of worldwide disaster \u2013 has been damaged. In response, Scrooge brings Della and Dewey to convince Von Drake's grown-up children that McDuck Enterprises can secure its contents, including the seeds of the Money Tree of Oramorris. Glomgold and Owlson arrive hoping to close the deal for th