 Birthday, Doofus Drake!\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      =  Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones & Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|9|4}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = 0.16<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-4-2019.html|title=UPDATED with Broadcast: SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 150 Wednesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.4.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=September 5, 2019|access-date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Scrooge discovers Louie has turned to Goldie for help in getting rich. Unsurprisingly, Goldie turns on Louie until she sees that he's invited to Doofus' birthday party and asks him to take her. They arrive pretending to be an aunt and nephew intending to take all of the million-dollar gift bags. However, Doofus sniffs out frauds among his guests and sends them to his \"Honey Bin\", leaving Louie and Goldie; Glomgold and his puppet-son; and Beaks and his robot-son, B.O.Y.D. (Nicolas Cantu). Once he removes Glomgold and Beaks, Doofus demands to know who ruined his party. Goldie blames Louie and Doofus has B.O.Y.D. attack him, but Goldie saves him. The party turns out to be a test, as Doofus claims Goldie as his new \"Gemeemama\". Louie's allowed to leave with the gift bags, but decides to rescue Goldie and give B.O.Y.D. to Doofus as a brother. B.O.Y.D. then transfers half of the fortune to his account for his new parents ([[Yuri Lowenthal]] & [[Tara Platt]]), allowing them to finally ground Doofus. During the confusion, Goldie steals the gift bags, but keeps a picture of Louie. Meanwhile, Della gets Huey out of his comfort zone in a video game. \n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 42\n |E